					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">OK it's great to know it's technically possible to test something on the N106 on the hardware. Then you have to :
<br />
<br />- Import a Namco game from japan using this mapper
<br />- Open this game and cut the epoxy blob containing the mapper
<br />- Find a host board that has a mapper that could be replaced by the N106 without too much modifications
<br />- Connect all wires to the host board
<br />
<br />Or alternatively :
<br />
<br />- Cut the epoxy blobs for both PRG-ROM and CHR-ROM on the game you imported, and somehow connect your own EPROMs/FLashROMs to them.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
